meanings.definition: To be of higher rank or importance than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: In our class, the teacher outranks the students.
meanings.sent2: The king outranks all the other nobles in the kingdom.
meanings.sent3: The cat thinks it outranks the dog in the house hierarchy.
meanings.sent4: Her kindness outranks her wealth in the eyes of the community.
meanings.sent5: The sun outranks all the stars in our solar system with its brightness.

meanings.definition: To surpass or exceed in rank or importance.
meanings.sent1: His speed outranks all the other runners in the race.
meanings.sent2: The new technology outranks the old methods in efficiency.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outranks the birds in the backyard for finding hidden nuts.
meanings.sent4: The student's dedication outranks his natural talent in achieving success.
meanings.sent5: The mountain peak outranks the surrounding hills in height and majesty.
